Remember the butternut squash…They’re pies now. 
Granny Sawda’s Butternut Squash Pie from Amethyst Ganaway @thizzg  I love this pie as much as I hate pumpkin pie (not sorry) and that’s a lot!
Granny Sawda’s Butternut Squash pie is the bright, cheerful, uplifting, life of the party antidote to the dull, dreary, over-spiced yet underwhelming pumpkin pies so common at this time of the year. It’s a fan favorite in this house. 🧡🥧🧡

Y’all! I created a cookie recipe for @washingtonpost ‘s @eatvoraciously 2022 Holiday Cookie Feature! 
It’s a Chocolate Raspberry Truffle Cookie dipped in red raspberry chocolate and dusted with gold. It’s inspired by a special box of truffles I received for Christmas when I was nine. 
I am beyond honored to be included in this annual Holiday feature with so many wonderful cooks and creators. 
I truly want to try every single recipe in this edition. To think my recipe could become even one someone’s cherished holiday tradition moves me to tears. ❤️ thank you to @becky.krystal and @eatvoraciously for including me in this showcase, making me and my cookies look so good, and giving me an opportunity to turn a sweet memory into something that has the potential to bring joy for generations to come. ♥️ 
Styling: @lisacherkasky 
Photos: @scottsuchman 

#ChefElrod #cookies #recipe #HolidayTradition
#pomegranate love ♥️

How it Started VS How it’s Going Holiday Cookie Edition Please enjoy some BTS views of my recipe development process making holiday cookies during the hottest days of summer. How hot? So hot my chocolate stayed melted at room temperature for hours! Please see the sweat on my decorated cookies for reference. But I didn’t let that stop me because I wanted to make this cookie something special to honor the memory of my maternal grandmother June’s creativity and generosity. She always made the holidays meaningful no matter how hard her daily struggles. And I wanted this recipe to evoke the joy I had in discovering how miraculous good chocolate in the right hands truly is. I hope I have done my grandmother and the chocolatiers who created that original box of Minerva Street Truffles justice. I truly hope this recipe brings holiday cheer into some of your homes. Thank you for letting me share myself and my passions with you. 
Big, fat, messy thank you to @becky.krystal and @eatvoraciously for inviting me to share something so meaningful with the world. 
Thanks to all the contributors for making this entire feature so beautiful, unique, and delicious to be a part of. @kimjoy @louisashafia @chabelacoss @thehangrywoman @sarahcarey1 @lahbco @bakerhands @tumblinbumblincrumblincookie @thejamlab @cheffrancisang @mayascookiessandiego @lopeariyo 
@washingtonpost Photography @scottsuchman Styling @lisacherkasky

Lately I’ve been roasting chicken with copious amounts of Illyanna Maisonet’s @burlapandbarrel collab Sazon and Adobo. This is the best sazon and adobo I’ve had and they’re salt free which means I can use as much as I want without over seasoning our food. The flavors are so well balanced and the brightness of the achiote is tantalizing. The hubs has been having stomach problems and he has no issues with these blends. In fact, they seem to make his stomach feel better! The chicken looks and tastes so beautiful, rich, and roasty. 
I use @wellspentmarket kosher sea salt for just the right salt level and that’s it. I need to order some more. Thanks for these blends @eatgordaeat 🧡 

#Sazon #Adobo #Diasporican #RoastChicken #ButlapandBarrel #ChefElrod #wellspentcommunity

♥️ Happy holiday season and merry Christmas eve my friends. 🎄
Holding the print edition of my @eatvoraciously holiday cookie recipe just hits different. I’ve achieved some things this year that I’ve been working towards my entire career. I’ve experienced some things I’ve waited for my entire life. I tend to downplay my achievements and big moments so as not to sound like I’m “bragging” but I don’t want to downplay the milestones and major achievements anymore because I rob myself and my loved ones of of the joy in them, and I lead others to believe I’m less than I am. 
I hope you are safe, warm, loved, and feeling celebratory tonight. I have more to share but will leave you with my love and good wishes for now. 🌟 ❤️ 🕯️

I was gonna make a recap reel but y’all, I just can’t do it. So please enjoy this pineapple and sour cherry upside down cake I made tonight. Pineapple upside down cake is my unequivocal jam. 
2022 has been a good year. In January I saw my first recipe published in a cookbook thanks to @rancho_gordo and in December I saw my first recipe published in a major newspaper thanks to @eatvoraciously and in between @beardfoundation awards, @cherrybombe Jubilee, @mofad @theafricacenter African American Food, plus many good times with many amazing culinary champions, friends, and loved ones, some long overdue travels, I even won some amazing giveaways, and I started a new teaching job! I really can’t recap it all. 
This year had its challenges but it’s the first year since 2018 (?) that had more highs than lows. 
I’m genuinely looking forward to all that 2023 holds. I
But for now pineapple upside down cake and rest. 
Wishing you all blessings, fulfillment, meaning, and rest in the new year! 
That’s a wrap ♥️ 

#chefelrod #lastpostof2022 #happynewyear2023 #lifeisgood #womeninfood

Arthur’s 1795 Market in historic Schenectady is exactly the kind of neighborhood place I dreamed about finding when we left NYC. It’s a lovely, low key cafe and shop with cookbooks, local food and beverages, cooking equipment, and more. In other words my favorite kind of place. The coffee, tea, and pastries are delicious and the atmosphere is great, with plenty of comfortable indoor and outdoor seating. They host cool events like their cookbook club too. 
I’m so happy to have a neighborhood place for a morning cup of coffee or in this case tea; they make a great London Fog latte and the molasses cookies are delicious. Pizza Man can vouch for the cinnamon rolls, sadly I didn’t get a pic.

Kicking off summer break with sheet tray nachos! They did not disappoint. How could they when they were covered in a king’s ransom’s worth of perfectly ripe avocado? 
We topped multi-grain scoops (you know those chips that are shaped like baskets, with a mix of sautéed chopped onion, ground chicken, and red beans seasoned with @cholulahotsauce taco seasoning, dark chili powder, granulated garlic, and onion. Then we topped that with grated cheddar, Monterey Jack, mozzarella cheeses, and finely chopped pickled jalapeños and cherry peppers. We broiled it all until bubbling and brown, then topped it all off with plenty of ripe avocado, and some sour cream. 
I added raw onion and cholula jalapeño hot sauce to some for me. 
Y’all life is too short to make reels. Really and truly. It took me less time to make this sheet tray full of nachos. How do people do this all the time? I used the trending audio too, ok? 
It’s summer break and a holiday weekend and these nachos got our party started. 💚 

#nachos #sheettraynachos #summerbreak #avocadoisking

Y’all I thought these golden kiwis (bottom right -swipe for more) were just some marketing ploy, but when I found them on sale curiosity got the better of me. They are not a marketing ploy, they are delicious. Their skin is thinner and less fuzzy than a green kiwi, they have less core, and their flesh is sweeter, milder, more yielding, kind of creamy and a little tangy. The flavor is almost reminiscent of a mango meets a banana. They are good! And they’re pretty too. ☀️ 🥝 They aren’t exactly local so I guess they’re for special occasions but they definitely add pizazz to a fruit salad and they’re delicious eaten with a spoon straight from the skin. 

#fruit #produce #NewToMeFruit
#GoldenKiwi #SunGoldKiwi #zesprisungold

chik’n parm, “nomato” sauce, and black rice noodles. Every once in awhile I toy around with a new iteration of nomato sauce. Every august I sit back and watch the tomato content roll by hot and heavy while I feel slightly sorry for myself. Why do I have to miss out on all the fun? 
Well, here’s my one contribution to the tomato content thanks to Jeff @libraryseedbank and @sparky.angela they are tomatoes with a distinguished pedigree. He kindly sent us some of his very special tomato seeds for our first garden. Unfortunately Pizza Man had to rescue and relocate what he could to save them from the voracious squirrels, possums, and skunks that roam our yard, so I’m no longer sure which varieties these are but they do look good basking in the glow of our window. And there’s your garden fresh  #tomato content so I can feel included and you can have what you really want. 🍅 you’re welcome. 

Image Description: Two homegrown tomatoes sit side by side on a yellow windowsill. The tomato to the left is dark red with a purple hue, the tomato to the right is bright red. They both have imperfections that make them obviously homegrown. The view through the window is of our green, grassy backyard blurred in the background. The afternoon sun hits the tomatoes from the left side. Their right sides in shadow. 
Three more slides show the tomatoes close up and from different angles.

#HomeGrown #TomatoSeason #518 #LibrarySeedBank #WindowSillTomatoes #Heirloom #SeedSavers #CapitalDistrict #ChefElrod

June 🩷 
Summer is almost officially over and school is back in session. Please allow me to recap the entire summer in three reels. 
June started in Chicago with @beardfoundation so many good friends, so much good food, and so much inspiration and it ended @hudsonvalleycc with the EOC students’ commencement which was a lot of fun and made me so proud. In between was my first magazine cover spotted in real life, my first cookbook collab announcement, and the first fruits of summer in our new home. 
Pizza Man stopped by our classroom to make pizza dough and sauce, I cooked, baked, and developed recipes. Kit Kat lounged, slept, and snacked through it all. It was a big, good month. 

Image Description: photos of food, people, and places Taffy visited and experienced during the month of June. 

#June2023 #SummerRecap #ChefElrod
#518 #CapitalDistrict #JBF2023 #Summer #Food

July 🧡 Less travel more food. Gifted black walnuts and a leg of lamb, the first fruits of our garden (three blackberries), lunch and an impromptu manicure with a friend, the NYC ballet as @spacsaratoga, a new ice cream machine at school, and student made donuts, finally getting my copy of Mayumu signed by Abi, books, owls, Kit Kat, rainbows, and the worst sundae I’ve ever been served, two bites and it went in the trash. What a month. 

Image description, a reel featuring a series of photos from July, mostly food and a few friends. 

#ChefElrod #SummerRecap #July #JulyRecap #CapitalDistrictNY #518 #FoodandFun

August 💙 
Friends, food, and fun. Visits from friends @the.cheftographer , day trips to Lake Sacandaga, Lake Luzerne, and Massachusetts, sourdough breads, a giant clafoutis, windowsill tomatoes from the yard, perfectly ripe, lush mangos and peaches together. Homegrown cucumber, I peeled the strawberry ok? , BBQ in Brooklyn, Pizza Man made pies for a party, Stewart’s ice cream in the back seat of our van, eclairs at school, always books, home became more homey, and then back to school to teach a new year of culinary experiences. And that’s a wrap on summer. Thanks for coming along for the ride. 

Image description: images of my august experiences the view from a boat on lake Sacandaga, a waterfall on the Hudson River in lake Luzerne, fresh baked bread in the light of the window, fruits, vegetables, my cat lounging, photos with friends, sunshine, rain, my husband Pizza Man making margarita pizzas and baking them in a wood burning oven outside a private home, and photos of me looking awkward and out of place in the great outdoors. 

#SummerRecap #August #NY #UpstateNY #adirondacks #Catskills #capitalregion #ChefElrod ##518 #Garden #Food

Belgian waffles made with my new sourdough starter. These were so light, crisp, and flavorful. But mostly just so light and crisp. The whole grain spelt flour was transformed by the proofing time into a light, creamy color and texture. 
I used about a cup and a half of starter to make a sponge with 2 cups of whole spelt flour, 1 cup of all purpose flour, 21/2 cups whole buttermilk, and two t
Tablespoons maple syrup. After the sponge proofed overnight I added 1/2 cup melted unsalted butter, three large eggs, 1/2 teaspoon sea salt, and 1/4 teaspoon baking soda. The longer I cooked them in the waffle iron the better they got. I always ignore the ready light anyway. 
I worked off of a recipe from @kingarthurbaking and made switches based on what I had and wanted to use. 
I will keep the extras in the freezer for quick meals and snacks. Fermented food rules. 

Image description: a reel made of photos and videos from my waffle making process, starting with a golden waffle, then showing the grayish, bubbly, sourdough sponge, the sponge with three eggs and a golden puddle of melted butter added, the black, Belgian waffle iron steaming after the batter was added, and opening the waffle iron to reveal the finished waffle, ending on a stack of waffles on a tray. 

#ChefElrod #CapitalDistrict #UpState #Sourdough #FermentedFoodsRule #Waffles #Spelt #NYFood #SergeGainsbourg #BelgianWaffles

I didn’t say it was gonna be a good reel everyday but I do make a damned good smoothie. Electrolytes, protein, probiotics, fiber and flavor from lots of fruit. I freeze them and Pizza Man takes them to work to beat the heat and stay hydrated doing intense physical work n this heat. They defrost in his backpack so he’s ready for lunch even in the middle of nowhere. Et voila there’s your reel for today (tonight) 

Image description: I made pink smoothies the video is a messy collection of photos and videos of the messy process. It shows the ingredients vanilla protein powder/meal replacement, probiotic shots, plain yogurt, coconut water, strawberries, mango, frozen melon, and frozen fafsa berry purée. the process of putting it in the blender, blending it, and pouring it into 16 Oz shaker cups. 

#ChefElrod #Reel #Smoothie #518 #CapitallDistrict #UpstateNY #Food #StayHydrated #PinkSmoothie

🌟 Cover Reveal 🌟 Hi friends, here’s the first look at The Juneteenth Cookbook. 
I developed the recipes for this special book with author Alliah Agostini @alliago and illustrator Sawyer Cloud @sawyercloud01 and it’s now available for Pre-order! 
The Juneteenth Cookbook will be available April 2024 just in time to start planning for your own Juneteenth celebration. I’m really proud to be a part of this and I can’t wait for you to see it, share it with your kids and family, and cook from it! 
I love the recipes we created for this book and it’s full of history, fun activities, and warm, welcoming illustrations that just make you feel good.
And stay tuned for more events and delicious fun to come surrounding the book. 
Working with these talented women on such a meaningful book was a dream come true. I am so excited for this book to be in the world and in the hands of littles who want to cook special foods, and you already know I developed these recipes to be delicious enough for Everyone at the cookout from the elders, to the cousins, to the babies, to the neighbors you weren’t expecting. 
Swipe through to see more and a little BTS peek at some of the recipes in the book. ♥️

I thought I’d share this moment of joy and gratitude in a long, difficult month. 
I found 99¢ pomegranates at our local market. Pizza Man gave them the ok, and went back for a bag full. He opened them and I helped remove the jewel like arils. We filled a 3 quart container. We still have a few more left. 
What an incredible luxury ♥️ also a moment of joy, comfort, love, and home. I can’t think of any other way to be of service right now than to share as much love as I can with anyone who is hurting. At the end of the day, that’s really all I’ve got.
Thanks @meemalee for reminding me to share this. 💖

My Black Caviar Lentil appetizer is back just in time for New Year’s Eve.

I’m dedicating 2024 to this girl. 
That’s my mom Suzy on the left and my (paternal) grandma Callie next to me. 
This picture was taken on a summer day in Michigan at a family reunion. 
It was also taken at the beginning of an end, one of the worst parts of my entire life. 2024 is for her, for me, for healing, and resolution, and making the way clear. Happy New Year.

2024 Day 1 Hoppin’ John with Collard Greens. 
This year the recipe for Hoppin’ John is my own. It will be in The Juneteenth Cookbook by Alliah Agostini recipes developed by yours truly. It was fun to cook the recipe again for the New Year. 
I added extra everything plus steamed collard greens to this batch. 🫘 🥬 
I don’t make resolutions as a general rule, but this year I am resolute in my determination to cook through the ingredients already in my pantry and develop more of my own recipes for publication. 

Happy New Year
